DURBAN - Durban's new solar project could be rolled out to the rest of the city.The eThekwini municipality says it's busy analysing the results from an initial project.Five municipal buildings are generating clean energy from solar panels mounted on their roofs.It includes the iconic Ushaka Marine World.The solar power project has reduced the city's carbon emissions by more than 40,000kg since December.It's also expected to lower energy costs by around R500,000 in the first year.eNCA